<subsection xml:id="subsec-Code-servo">
  <title>Code</title>
  <term>Source Code</term>
  <program>
    #include&lt;Servo.h&gt;
      Servo motor;
      int IRSensor=3;
      void setup()
      {
      Serial.begin(9600);
      motor.attach(9);
      pinMode(IRSensor, INPUT);
      }
      void loop ()
      {
      int statusSensor=digitalRead(IRSensor);
      if(statusSensor==1)
      {
      motor.write(90);
      delay (1000);
      Serial.println("okay");
      }      
      delay (1000);
}
  </program>
  <term>Code Explanation</term>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        First, we should install the library for servo motor. Library installation is given in chapter 1.3
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Declaring pins of IR sensor and servo motor to 3rd and 9th pins of Arduino respectively. 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Declaring servo motor function as servo motor. 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        In void setup function declaring motor using motor for example, Attach (9). 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Initializing the IR sensor as input using PinMode function. 
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        In void loop function the value of IR sensor will be stored digital data using digital Read function.
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        When the sensor finds the object the, it will be set to high, when it is high the motor will rotate for 90 degrees with the delay of 1 milli second. The 90-degree rotation will open the door. 
      </p>
    </li>
  </ol>
</subsection>
